# AWS CDK Guidelines

## Project Structure
- Organize code with proper stack and construct patterns
- Use appropriate directory structure for stacks
- Implement proper environment configuration
- Follow naming conventions for constructs
- Separate infrastructure from application code

## Constructs
- Create reusable constructs for common patterns
- Use appropriate construct scope and id patterns
- Implement proper construct properties
- Follow construct best practices
- Document construct usage and parameters

## Stacks
- Organize infrastructure into logical stacks
- Implement proper stack dependencies
- Use appropriate stack parameters
- Follow naming conventions for stacks
- Handle cross-stack references properly

## Resources
- Use high-level constructs when available
- Implement proper resource configuration
- Follow AWS best practices for resources
- Use appropriate resource properties
- Handle resource dependencies correctly

## Configuration
- Use appropriate environment variables
- Implement proper account and region configuration
- Handle different environments (dev/staging/prod)
- Use context values for configuration
- Follow security best practices for configuration

## Security
- Implement proper IAM roles and policies
- Use managed policies when possible
- Follow principle of least privilege
- Handle secrets appropriately
- Use encryption for sensitive data

## Testing
- Write comprehensive unit tests for constructs
- Use snapshot testing for infrastructure
- Test different configuration scenarios
- Validate infrastructure changes
- Follow testing best practices

## Deployment
- Use appropriate deployment strategies
- Implement proper CI/CD pipelines
- Handle stack updates safely
- Use change sets for validation
- Follow deployment best practices

## Cost Optimization
- Use appropriate instance types
- Implement proper resource tagging
- Monitor resource costs
- Use reserved capacity when appropriate
- Follow cost optimization best practices

## Monitoring and Logging
- Implement proper CloudWatch monitoring
- Use appropriate logging patterns
- Set up alerting for critical metrics
- Monitor resource usage
- Follow observability best practices

## Environment Management
- Use appropriate AWS accounts for environments
- Implement proper environment isolation
- Handle cross-environment dependencies
- Use environment-specific configurations
- Follow multi-account best practices

## Asset Management
- Handle Lambda functions and assets properly
- Use appropriate asset bundling strategies
- Implement proper asset versioning
- Optimize asset sizes
- Follow security best practices for assets